[src:nixos/manual-nixos-p02] Please consider using Userborn over systemd-sysusers as it’s more feature complete.
[src:nixos/manual-nixos-p02] The primary benefit of this is to remove a dependency on perl.
[src:nixos/manual-nixos-p02] It can update some information about users.
[src:nixos/manual-nixos-p02] Most notably it can update their passwords.
[src:nixos/manual-nixos-p02] It will warn when users use an insecure or unsupported password hashing scheme.
[src:nixos/manual-nixos-p02] Userborn is the recommended way to manage users if you don’t want to rely on the Perl script.
[src:nixos/manual-nixos-p02] It aims to eventually replace the Perl script by default.
[src:nixos/manual-nixos-p02] This is useful when you store `/etc` on a `tmpfs` or if `/etc` is immutable (e.g. when using `system.etc.overlay.mutable = false;`).
